verses.text_plain: And it came to pass after these things, that the butler of the king of Egypt and his baker had offended their lord the king of Egypt.
verses.verse_html: 1And it came to pass after these things, that the butler of the king of Egypt and his baker had offended their lord the king of Egypt.

tokens.text: And it came to pass after

verses.text_plain: And Pharaoh was wroth against two of his officers, against the chief of the butlers, and against the chief of the bakers.
verses.verse_html: 2And Pharaoh was wroth against two of his officers, against the chief of the butlers, and against the chief of the bakers.

verses.text_plain: And he put them in ward in the house of the captain of the guard, into the prison, the place where Joseph was bound.
verses.verse_html: 3And he put them in ward in the house of the captain of the guard, into the prison, the place where Joseph was bound.

verses.text_plain: And the captain of the guard charged Joseph with them, and he served them: and they continued a season in ward.
verses.verse_html: 4And the captain of the guard charged Joseph with them, and he served them: and they continued a season in ward.

tokens.text: them: and they continued a season

verses.text_plain: And they dreamed a dream both of them, each man his dream in one night, each man according to the interpretation of his dream, the butler and the baker of the king of Egypt, which were bound in the prison.
verses.verse_html: 5And they dreamed a dream both of them, each man his dream in one night, each man according to the interpretation of his dream, the butler and the baker of the king of Egypt, which were bound in the prison.

verses.text_plain: And Joseph came in unto them in the morning, and looked upon them, and, behold, they were sad.
verses.verse_html: 6And Joseph came in unto them in the morning, and looked upon them, and, behold, they were sad.

verses.text_plain: And he asked Pharaohs officers that were with him in the ward of his lords house, saying, Wherefore look ye so sadly to day?
verses.verse_html:
7And he asked Pharaohs officers that were with him in the ward of his lords house, saying, Wherefore look ye so sadly to day?
 look: Heb. are your faces evil?

footnotes.body_text: look: Heb. are your faces evil?
footnotes.body_html: look: Heb. are your faces evil?

verses.text_plain: And they said unto him, We have dreamed a dream, and there is no interpreter of it. And Joseph said unto them, Do not interpretations belong to God? tell me them, I pray you.
verses.verse_html: 8And they said unto him, We have dreamed a dream, and there is no interpreter of it. And Joseph said unto them, Do not interpretations belong to God? tell me them, I pray you.

verses.text_plain: And the chief butler told his dream to Joseph, and said to him, In my dream, behold, a vine was before me;
verses.verse_html: 9And the chief butler told his dream to Joseph, and said to him, In my dream, behold, a vine was before me;

verses.text_plain: And in the vine were three branches: and it was as though it budded, and her blossoms shot forth; and the clusters thereof brought forth ripe grapes:
verses.verse_html: 10And in the vine were three branches: and it was as though it budded, and her blossoms shot forth; and the clusters thereof brought forth ripe grapes:

verses.text_plain: And Pharaohs cup was in my hand: and I took the grapes, and pressed them into Pharaohs cup, and I gave the cup into Pharaohs hand.
verses.verse_html: 11And Pharaohs cup was in my hand: and I took the grapes, and pressed them into Pharaohs cup, and I gave the cup into Pharaohs hand.

verses.text_plain: And Joseph said unto him, This is the interpretation of it: The three branches are three days:
verses.verse_html: 12And Joseph said unto him, This is the interpretation of it: The three branches are three days:

verses.text_plain: Yet within three days shall Pharaoh lift up thine head, and restore thee unto thy place: and thou shalt deliver Pharaohs cup into his hand, after the former manner when thou wast his butler.
verses.verse_html:
13Yet within three days shall Pharaoh lift up thine head, and restore thee unto thy place: and thou shalt deliver Pharaohs cup into his hand, after the former manner when thou wast his butler.
 lift: or, reckon

verses.text_plain: But think on me when it shall be well with thee, and shew kindness, I pray thee, unto me, and make mention of me unto Pharaoh, and bring me out of this house:
verses.verse_html:
14But think on me when it shall be well with thee, and shew kindness, I pray thee, unto me, and make mention of me unto Pharaoh, and bring me out of this house:
 think: Heb. remember me with thee

tokens.text: on me when it shall be well
I pray thee, unto me, and make mention

footnotes.body_text: think: Heb. remember me with thee
footnotes.body_html: think: Heb. remember me with thee

verses.text_plain: For indeed I was stolen away out of the land of the Hebrews: and here also have I done nothing that they should put me into the dungeon.
verses.verse_html: 15For indeed I was stolen away out of the land of the Hebrews: and here also have I done nothing that they should put me into the dungeon.

tokens.text: For indeed I was stolen away
and here also have I done

verses.text_plain: When the chief baker saw that the interpretation was good, he said unto Joseph, I also was in my dream, and, behold, I had three white baskets on my head:
verses.verse_html:
16When the chief baker saw that the interpretation was good, he said unto Joseph, I also was in my dream, and, behold, I had three white baskets on my head:
 white: or, full of holes

footnotes.body_html: white: or, full of holes

verses.text_plain: And in the uppermost basket there was of all manner of bakemeats for Pharaoh; and the birds did eat them out of the basket upon my head.
verses.verse_html:
17And in the uppermost basket there was of all manner of bakemeats for Pharaoh; and the birds did eat them out of the basket upon my head.
 bakemeats: Heb. meat of Pharaoh, the work of a baker, or, cook

footnotes.body_text: bakemeats: Heb. meat of Pharaoh, the work of a baker, or, cook
footnotes.body_html: bakemeats: Heb. meat of Pharaoh, the work of a baker, or, cook

verses.text_plain: And Joseph answered and said, This is the interpretation thereof: The three baskets are three days:
verses.verse_html: 18And Joseph answered and said, This is the interpretation thereof: The three baskets are three days:

verses.text_plain: Yet within three days shall Pharaoh lift up thy head from off thee, and shall hang thee on a tree; and the birds shall eat thy flesh from off thee.
verses.verse_html:
19Yet within three days shall Pharaoh lift up thy head from off thee, and shall hang thee on a tree; and the birds shall eat thy flesh from off thee.
 lift: or, reckon thee, and take thy office from thee

tokens.text: from off thee, and shall hang

footnotes.body_text: lift: or, reckon thee, and take thy office from thee
footnotes.body_html: lift: or, reckon thee, and take thy office from thee

verses.text_plain: And it came to pass the third day, which was Pharaohs birthday, that he made a feast unto all his servants: and he lifted up the head of the chief butler and of the chief baker among his servants.
verses.verse_html:
20And it came to pass the third day, which was Pharaohs birthday, that he made a feast unto all his servants: and he lifted up the head of the chief butler and of the chief baker among his servants.
 lifted: or, reckoned

tokens.text: And it came to pass the third

verses.text_plain: And he restored the chief butler unto his butlership again; and he gave the cup into Pharaohs hand:
verses.verse_html: 21And he restored the chief butler unto his butlership again; and he gave the cup into Pharaohs hand:

verses.text_plain: But he hanged the chief baker: as Joseph had interpreted to them.
verses.verse_html: 22But he hanged the chief baker: as Joseph had interpreted to them.

verses.text_plain: Yet did not the chief butler remember Joseph, but forgat him.
verses.verse_html: 23Yet did not the chief butler remember Joseph, but forgat him.
